Jsx:
const heading=<h1 className="site-setting"> Hello, React </h1>

No Jsx:
const heading= React.createElement('h1',{className:'site-heading'},'Hello-React')

Internally React uses this createElement method, even when we use jsx.





               Differences
       HTML                  JSX
       
       class                 className
       onclick               onClick
       <img>                 <img/>
       
       To use a variable into a jsx:
       Ex: const name= 'Tanya';
           const heading= <h1> Hello {name} </h1>
